      "tree": {
        "sha": "034c0e37b3fe745ba4d3ade04130cd9d15f1db88",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/034c0e37b3fe745ba4d3ade04130cd9d15f1db88"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 034c0e37b3fe745ba4d3ade04130cd9d15f1db88\nparent d868667fdc534c7ac04d4348c31a50e26679ef34\nauthor Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com> 1775588229 +0300\ncommitter Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com> 1775589379 +0300\n\nrefactor: simplify stream rewind\n\n`DataStream::Rewind()` supported partial rewinds and a failure return value, but the remaining users only need a full reset to the start of the buffered bytes.\n\nReplace it with `rewind()` and update the prevector benchmark accordingly.\nThis keeps the stream API closer to its current use and removes stateful behavior that the follow-up cleanup no longer needs.\n",
